"1110":"1110","1197":"1197","1097":"1097","1196":"1196","1094":"1094","Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk","Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Frankrijk","Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Frankreich":"Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Frankrijk","Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Frankrijk"},"en":{"1097–1149":"1097–1149","1110–1149":"1110–1149","1129–1197":"1129–1197","1139–1196":"1139–1196","1069–1118":"1069–1118","1078–1143":"1078–1143","1118":"1118","1129":"1129","1139":"1139","1149":"1149","1069":"1069","1078":"1078","1143":"1143","1110":"1110","1197":"1197","1097":"1097","1196":"1196","1094":"1094","Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France","Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Frankreich":"Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France","Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Rigobert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["From a Germanic name composed of the elements <i>rīc</i> ‘power’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, shining, famous’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Violet  ,   Vivien  , or   Vivian ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Rigobert II d'Angres was born in 1097, in Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France, his father, Léon II d'Angres, was 28 and his mother, Claude d'Olhain, was 19. He married Marta d'Aubigny in Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. He died in 1149, at the age of 52."},"et":{"1097–1149":"1097–1149","1110–1149":"1110–1149","1129–1197":"1129–1197","1139–1196":"1139–1196","1069–1118":"1069–1118","1078–1143":"1078–1143","1118":"1118","1129":"1129","1139":"1139","1149":"1149","1069":"1069","1078":"1078","1143":"1143","1110":"1110","1197":"1197","1097":"1097","1196":"1196","1094":"1094","Angres, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Lens, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Frankreich":"Aubigny-en-Artois, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Angres, Pas-de